They know the truth.

1056
01:20:33,047 --> 01:20:35,800
They can't afford to face it.

1057
01:20:35,887 --> 01:20:39,084
It's a war.
You're one if its innocent victims.

1058
01:20:39,167 --> 01:20:41,247
I'm sorry for your trouble.

1059
01:20:41,247 --> 01:20:43,317
Don't be sorry for us.

1060
01:20:43,607 --> 01:20:45,882
You should be sorry
for the people you killed.

1061
01:20:47,647 --> 01:20:50,684
It was a military target,
a soldier's pub.

1062
01:20:50,767 --> 01:20:55,247
They were innocent people,
God's children.

1063
01:20:55,247 --> 01:20:59,877
Look, I'll do all I can
to help you while you're in here.

1064
01:20:59,967 --> 01:21:01,241
We don't need your help.

1065
01:21:03,127 --> 01:21:05,595
I'd appreciate it
if you'd leave us alone.

1066
01:21:06,967 --> 01:21:08,320
Whatever you say.

1067
01:21:11,247 --> 01:21:13,238
I'm sorry about that.

1068
01:21:17,207 --> 01:21:19,243
What was that all about?
You mind your fucking manners.

1069
01:21:19,287 --> 01:21:23,963
What? Manners to him? I don't want
any part of him, or his ways.

1070
01:21:24,047 --> 01:21:27,247
At least he fights back, which is
more than you ever did in your life.

1071
01:21:27,247 --> 01:21:29,841
- What are you talking about?
- Do you remember Lydon Hill?

1072
01:21:29,927 --> 01:21:32,725
You used to ride me up
on your bike up Lydon Hill.

1073
01:21:32,807 --> 01:21:34,798
And then one day
you couldn't make it to the top...

1074
01:21:34,887 --> 01:21:39,247
and I hopped off and looked back,
and your face was all red.

1075
01:21:39,247 --> 01:21:41,283
- Remember that?
- Aye.

1076
01:21:44,247 --> 01:21:46,556
It was working in the paint shed
done that to you.

1077
01:21:46,647 --> 01:21:47,921
What?

1078
01:21:48,007 --> 01:21:51,602
It was the fumes from working
in the paint shed done that to you.

1079
01:21:51,687 --> 01:21:54,155
Never mind jumping off the ferry,
swimming back to Mammy.

1080
01:21:54,247 --> 01:21:57,762
It was the one job a Catholic can get,
and you wouldn't even fight back then.

1081
01:21:57,847 --> 01:22:02,967
Go on outside.
Play with your newfound friend.

1082
01:22:03,047 --> 01:22:07,199
All I'm saying is that you've been
a victim. It's time you fought back.

1083
01:22:07,247 --> 01:22:08,999
- Get out of my sight.
- I'm going.

1084
01:22:11,927 --> 01:22:15,237
This is the only way it'll work.
We have no alternative.

1085
01:22:32,247 --> 01:22:35,284
- Well, what are you doing?
- Nothing.

1086
01:22:36,847 --> 01:22:39,645
- They didn't do it.
- They all did it.

1087
01:22:43,247 --> 01:22:45,238
I'm going back to Belfast.

1088
01:22:51,807 --> 01:22:55,641
After the fight, nobody stopped us
going out in the yard to exercise.

1089
01:22:55,727 --> 01:22:59,083
I felt brilliant.
Joe explained things to me.

1090
01:22:59,167 --> 01:23:02,159
He explained how the Brits
never left anywhere without a fight...

1091
01:23:02,247 --> 01:23:05,637
how they had to be beaten out of
every country they ever occupied...

1092
01:23:05,727 --> 01:23:09,083
how this prison was just
an extension of their system.

1093
01:23:09,167 --> 01:23:11,601
Calling for work
on the threes.

1094
01:23:11,687 --> 01:23:14,724
We had to confront the chief
prison officer, Barker.

1095
01:23:14,807 --> 01:23:16,247
Mr Smalls.

1096
01:23:16,247 --> 01:23:19,247
But to do that,
we had to take care of Ronnie Smalls.

1097
01:23:19,247 --> 01:23:22,239
Can I have a word
about 54 Halsley Road?

1098
01:23:26,007 --> 01:23:27,884
Take a walk.

1099
01:23:35,247 --> 01:23:38,956
If anything happens to me
or Gerry...

1100
01:23:39,727 --> 01:23:42,247
or any other Irish prisoner...

1101
01:23:42,247 --> 01:23:46,604
we'll have 54 Halsley Road
blown to smithereens...

1102
01:23:46,687 --> 01:23:49,565
