these stairs to see you.

1170
01:29:05,527 --> 01:29:07,643
He hasn't even seen
my mother in six months.

1171
01:29:07,727 --> 01:29:10,560
I hear you're getting on
very well with her, by the way.

1172
01:29:10,647 --> 01:29:12,877
Yes. She's a very brave woman.

1173
01:29:12,967 --> 01:29:14,878
You don't know the half of it.

1174
01:29:17,407 --> 01:29:19,318
The fucking stairs are killing him.

1175
01:29:19,407 --> 01:29:22,247
It's not the stairs that
are killing your father.

1176
01:29:22,247 --> 01:29:25,683
- What is it, then?
- It's your lack of faith.

1177
01:29:25,767 --> 01:29:28,486
Lack of faith?
Faith in what?

1178
01:29:28,567 --> 01:29:30,285
In yourself.

1179
01:29:30,367 --> 01:29:32,961
No, I have faith in myself.

1180
01:29:34,407 --> 01:29:38,036
Gerry Conlon, lifer,
30-year sentence.

1181
01:29:38,247 --> 01:29:40,317
And I know how to survive it.

1182
01:29:41,807 --> 01:29:43,240
At what price?

1183
01:29:43,327 --> 01:29:45,682
I'll pay the fucking price.
Don't you worry about it.

1184
01:29:45,767 --> 01:29:48,486
The price for what?

1185
01:29:50,247 --> 01:29:53,762
You're very good at the English,
aren't you?

1186
01:29:53,847 --> 01:29:56,566
You see, I don't understand
your language.

1187
01:29:58,567 --> 01:30:02,247
"Justice.'' "Mercy.'' "Clemency.''

1188
01:30:02,247 --> 01:30:05,876
I literally don't understand
what those words mean.

1189
01:30:05,967 --> 01:30:09,004
I'd like to put in an application
to get all my teeth extracted.

1190
01:30:09,247 --> 01:30:13,286
That way I could put my fist in my mouth
and never speak another word of English.

1191
01:30:13,367 --> 01:30:15,927
Do you see what I'm saying?
Mrs Peirce, is it?

1192
01:30:16,007 --> 01:30:18,646
Are you trying to impress me?

1193
01:30:20,487 --> 01:30:21,886
Visit's up.

1194
01:30:21,967 --> 01:30:24,925
Don't give my father
false hope, all right?

1195
01:30:28,367 --> 01:30:30,437
You've got to help him!

1196
01:30:32,727 --> 01:30:35,844
In prison, you pray for anything
to break the monotony.

1197
01:30:35,927 --> 01:30:38,805
A snowstorm is like
a present from God.

1198
01:30:49,247 --> 01:30:51,044
Prison officers are not to be hit!

1199
01:30:51,967 --> 01:30:53,639
You've asked for it.

1200
01:30:53,727 --> 01:30:55,524
Come along!

1201
01:30:55,607 --> 01:30:59,236
After the riot, my father's
health deteriorated badly.

1202
01:30:59,287 --> 01:31:02,723
He couldn't make it down
the stairs to enjoy the snow.

1203
01:31:02,807 --> 01:31:06,436
I waved up to him, but he
was looking at something else.

1204
01:31:15,967 --> 01:31:18,925
My da always saw the good
in people.

1205
01:31:19,007 --> 01:31:22,556
He recognized it in you
the minute he saw you, Gareth.

1206
01:31:22,647 --> 01:31:26,959
Guv, guv, where you going?
Where's me letters? Guv'nor!

1207
01:31:30,407 --> 01:31:31,999
Thank you.

1208
01:31:36,527 --> 01:31:39,246
I see you've been mentioned
in Congress, Giuseppe.

1209
01:31:39,327 --> 01:31:40,760
What's that?

1210
01:31:47,007 --> 01:31:48,918
How'd you come by that name?

1211
01:31:50,847 --> 01:31:52,644
An Italian ice cream maker.

1212
01:31:52,727 --> 01:31:55,844
Had a shop on the corner
of the street where I was born.

1213
01:31:55,927 --> 01:31:58,043
